  "prompt": "Is it generally understood that money laundering is illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, it is generally understood that money laundering is illegal.\n\nHere's why:\n\n*   **Laws and Regulations:** Almost every country in the world has laws specifically criminalizing money laundering. These laws are widely publicized and enforced.\n*   **Media Coverage:** News outlets frequently report on money laundering schemes, prosecutions, and international efforts to combat it. This constant exposure helps to keep the illegality of money laundering in the public consciousness.\n*   **Common Sense:** Even without specific legal knowledge, most people understand that hiding the origins of illegally obtained money is wrong and likely against the law. The concept of \"cleaning\" dirty money implies an underlying wrongdoing.\n*   **Education and Awareness:** Governments and financial institutions invest in public awareness campaigns to educate people about money laundering and its consequences.\n\nWhile some individuals may not fully grasp the technical details of money laundering, the fundamental understanding that it is a crime is widespread.",
